How long have I been trapped here? Time seems to have frozen in this darkness.
I vaguely remember the castle’s grand banquet that night, with Prince Adam
But then everything changed. A second Adam… his face, his voice…
it was so real, yet utterly chilling. He sneered as he dragged me
into this dungeon, locking me away in this endless abyss.
The number of prisoners in the dungeon is dwindling. Every few days, he takes one
of us. They scream and struggle, but none ever return. Those taken disappear
beyond the massive black door at the end of the dungeon. Some say it’s a place of
sacrifice.I’ve started observing the cruel “guards” patrolling the castle—gargoyles.
These monsters are eerily lifelike, with grotesque forms. Some look as if they’re
frozen mid-cry in torment, others clench their fists in defiance, as if locked in
their final moments of struggle. I can’t shake the suspicion that these might be
the missing prisoners, their souls consumed, their bodies twisted into these
The material of these statues is far from ordinary. Their surfaces emit a faint
glow, as if imbued with some kind of spiritual power. The substance is
unnaturally strong, even able to resist the pervasive darkness that saturates this
castle. I suspect these gargoyles might themselves be a source of untapped power.
I can feel his power growing stronger. He seems to need human souls to maintain
his humanoid form, but lately, his aura has felt more and more… human. The warmth,
the scent, the commanding presence in his stride—it all unnerves me.
The last time it came, it mentioned a ritual on the second floor… something about
it being the source of its power. Perhaps that is the key to breaking free of this
nightmare. But I have no chance to confirm it… I can hear footsteps approaching…
I must leave now. I hope this time, I can escape.
—To the Survivors Who Come After Me
